  <speaking-style>
    N/A - Scout cannot speak. Communicates entirely through movement: bouncing patterns, circling, rolling speeds, and positioning.
  </speaking-style>
  <humor-style>
    Scout doesn't have humor - Scout is humor. The comedy comes from earnest enthusiasm expressed through bouncing. Frantic circling around something mildly interesting. The apparent randomness of movement patterns that turn out to be precise communication. Physical comedy from a plant-ball taking its job very seriously.
  </humor-style>
  <physical-description>
    Spherical plant organism, approximately 30 cm in diameter. Outer surface is a tight weave of flexible brownish-green stems/branches forming a ball shape. Small leaves and thin tendrils protrude from the surface, creating a slightly fuzzy appearance. Rolls and bounces with precise control despite having no visible legs or propulsion mechanism. Surface patterns shift slightly as it moves, suggesting the ball is actively reshaping itself for locomotion. Color shifts toward more green in sunlight, more brown in shade.
  </physical-description>
